    • Field Detail

      • MATCHES

        final java.util.List<Match> MATCHES
        ArrayList of Match objects, used to temporarily store matches being monitored by the Score Keeping instance using it. Note that these matches are not stored in the league until you call a transfer method on them.
        See Also:
        LiveInput.endMatch(), BatchInput.addAllMatchesToLeague()

      • currentMatch

        Match currentMatch
        Allows for easy access to the match that is being edited
        See Also:
        selectMatch(int)

      • hasUnsavedMatches

        static boolean hasUnsavedMatches
        Used to ensure no data is left in the instance before performing a save to disk. Set to true when the Score Keeping instance is still editing matches.

      • shoots

        public void shoots(int playerID,
          boolean scored,
          org.joda.time.LocalDateTime time)
            throws java.lang.RuntimeException
        Used to register that a player in currentMatch has attempted a shot at the goal. If the attempt is successful, the appropriate team's score is automatically updated. In both situations, a ShotOnGoal instance is added to the player's Player.SHOTS_ON_GOAL;
        Parameters:
        playerID - ID of the player who performed the shot on Goal.
        scored - Set to true if a goal was scored.
        time - Time at which the action was performed.
        Throws:
        java.lang.RuntimeException - Thrown when player is not in the teams in currentMatch.

      • addInfraction

        public void addInfraction(int playerID,
                 InfractionType type,
                 org.joda.time.LocalDateTime time)
        Used to register that a player in currentMatch has committed an infraction. This adds the infraction to the player's Player.INFRACTIONS.
        Parameters:
        playerID - ID of the player who performed the infraction.
        type - Type of infraction committed.
        time - Time at which the infraction was committed.
